Rating: 4
After reading all of the GREAT reviews, I just had to make this for my family's July4 BBQ!!! Since it sounded so amazingly good, and my family is large (and loves to eat!) I made 2. I used an Oreo crust for one, graham cracker crust for the other (only 4 TBS butter for OREO, the full stick for graham) I also topped the cheesecake with a sour cream topping (2 c. sour cream, 1/4 c. sugar, 1 1/2 tsp vanilla) before decorating with fruit. Couldn't find good raspberries, so used strawberries. Also did a blueberry star on one, surrounded with cut strawberries, and a strawberry star one the other, with a blueberry border and sprinkled blueberries around the star. They were beautiful and the most DELICIOUS cheesecake anyone had ever had! I took a picture, is there any way I can post it?

