Rating: 2
I have to say I thought this was just okay. I didn't really like the texture, thought it tasted a bit bland, and the crust was soft - not soggy, but not crisp. The white chocolate cheesecake on this site is wonderful, and uses the same crust but bakes it about 10 minutes before filling, so it's harder. I think I'll try this again, but use a water bath next time which should improve the creaminess, as well as baking the crust first. My cake also split terribly on the top, which was covered by the topping, but the water bath might help with that, too. Also, I'll make sure my zest is very fine; I always use zest the same way as I did in making this, but this time the texture of it really stood out, and I didn't like that. By the way, I brought it to a party and everyone loved it -- it was just picky me that didn't because I know I can do better.

